@oue Are you trying to use the `dealias_fourdd` function on this file?  

Py-ART does not seem to have an issue reading the visualizing this file but it does run into some issue if you try to unwrap the Doppler velocities using this function.  Some of these issues are caused by these files not following the CfRadial conventions for file layout.  These include using text and not a float to specify the `meters_between_gates` and `meters_to_center_of_first_gate` attributes of the range variable.  Also many of the instrument parameters variable, including the nyquist_velocity, are scalar where-as CfRadial requires that these have dimensional of time.  

Even fixing these the `dealias_fourdd` function will not work at the moment as it currently does not play nicely with volumes where one or more rays are not included in a sweep (some rays are "in transition").

